A great app for those who like to explore and preplan routes for walking and cycling.

random places.

it's fantastic for riding!

However there are a few downsides.
· No offline maps.
It seems like Komoot has very few areas available to use offline.
Even though I bought “the world”, I cannot use it.
· The map works slowly-ish on even on new devices with powerful hardware.
· The ads are annoying, they make want to uninstall.

Only thing missing for me is a breakdown of times per km or mile.
I have to use another app for that but I'd rather have it all on Komoot.
When you're training it's really good to know how much you're improving.

Fantastic app.
My family and I are visiting the Alps and despite having walked plenty of times in the UK, know next to nothing about the routes in the Alps.
This app has guided us through walks both high on mountain tops and in lowland in forests.
It gives step by step directions amd completely takes the stress out of navigation.
Sure its best to have a map as back up, but I haven't had to rely on anything other than this app on this trip.
Finally a hiking app that is awesome!
I will always use it and much better than All Trails app.

Getting us London to Istanbul.

I agree with specifics in other critical reviews.

I like the way it shows the path surfaces, we often replan if we see a smoother alternative!
Whether it's bike riding in my home city of Greenville South Carolina or taking this app with me to the far reaches of the world (Lucca, Italy, Barcelona) I love this app.
Easy to use and allows me to change different modes from hiking to biking.
I love the ability of creating a route in the app will look for optimal route based on mode of transportation.
It also gives you the ability of editing the route.
Very well done!

Words also cannot describe how much I have zero interest in "Joe Bloggs went on hike" I want to permanently hide or remove that social media nonsense too.

Despite being a good app, doesn't allow to avoid certain kinds of paths like bike commute lanes (pretty dangerous in my city cuz you share it with pedestrians), causing longer and no efficient routes for someone that really wants to train, plus if you don't configure the route in a web browser is almost impossible to really get what you want.
Take into account that the safe route is the fast route, not the one that could get you get robbed, or cause you delays while training.
No way to store plan for offline usage.
Get prompt to allow access in settings, only to find out it has access to photos and videos already, and there is no option to grant external storage.
So app just complains that you need to grant access which you can't give.
Could be app not updated for this version of Android.
This app will take you down potentially dangerous and sometimes impossible routes.
It doesn't seem to know the difference between touring and hiking or mountain biking.
The worst was taking us through a hiking trail into someone's orange Grove to a locked gate we had to throw out stuff over.
We would have turned back if it wasn't for the scary dogs let loose at the last property we hurridly biked away from.
This app needs a function where you can select "no paths" or etc.
Also drains my battery
Login failed to accept my password stored in Chrome.
Password reset email did not arrive.
Unclear as to what you are paying for.
When I finally followed a circular walk, I found 1/2 way round that the sea had long ago washed away part of the path.
Great app to find more mountain bike trails but there is one feature I think is missing.
If you crash on your bike, no one will know.
Would be great to see a feature that detects impact and no longer moving and sends a text to let someone know where you are through GPS.
If Komoot had this, a lot more mountain bikers would have it.
Will it be possible to include more statistical data after each trip?
e.g.
average and maxinum speed, and filter by distance.
I am giving 4 stars because komoot on Samsung watch does not work well, cannot always connect to GPS and basically useless..
Very good app with very handy features.
One bug I discovered: On Android 12 the app doesn't keep the path to the external storage (SD-card) map although it's being used properly.
As soon as you restart the phone (Android 12) the initial setting (internal memory) is being used again.
Developer or support feedback is very much appreciated, tnx a lot!

DON'T WASTE YOUR MONEY ON PREMIUM, I just got done trying to use the premium version of the app for an 800+ mile bike trip through Michigan, Wisconsin, and Illinois and this app absolutely made everything more frustrating.
It tells you the wrong information for trail conditions, it would tell me 3 miles for instance of non paved roads yet I would find myself on 15-20 miles of it per day with their navigation.
I switched to Google maps halfway through the trip and it was a much better result
Quite good maps and they show quite accurately proper cycling routes.
I wish more possibility to see commodity places like cafes, camping sites, etc.
However, off line map downloading got stuck when I tried to remove one map and download another same time.
Probably should not cleared map cache at the same time.
Edit: I have found somewhat annoying bug.
I have electric bicycle.
When I stop recording I select to save road ride with electric assist but it is actually not saved with that option.
Komoot is so useful for tracking and storing all my cycling outings, I can record a new random ride and then simply be guided along next time I want to go around that same route.
I'm find it so simple and easy to use.
Still exploring the many options available, but looks to be my go to cycling app now!!
Coming from a Tizen based Galaxy 3 watch to a Galaxy 5 was really disappointed how many features have been cut out of the watch app.
No map mode is a big deal breaker.
Can't circle through distance done or distance remaining, time done or time remaining and other features.
Big disappointment for such a good navigation app
The bar at the top showing the distance doesn't update which makes the navigation not much useful.
(it shows you turn right in 1km when you actually need to turn right).
I've tried to reinstall the app, restart the phone, clear the cache and nothing has helped.
I've reported it to the customer service so we will see
I'm giving up my subscription and switching to Garmin because during navigating it switches back to North instead of the direction you're going creating dangerous and very irritant moments.
I basically had enough of this basic error that does not seem to get fixed.
Very good app to get ideas for hiking and running routes and even record your activity with detailed statistics.
Some features are behind a paywall though like recording cycling workouts but the free version offers plenty!
The app is great for planning an A to B route.
However it is a complete pain if you want to plan your own route using waypoints.
